@page "/components/hxselect"

<h1>@nameof(HxSelect<object, object>)</h1>
<p class="lead">
	Single-item picker.
</p>

<h3>Properties</h3>
<ul>
	<li>
		<strong>@nameof(HxSelect<object, object>.AutoSort)</strong><br />
		When true, items are sorted before displaying in select. Default value is <code>true</code>.
	</li>
	<li>
		<strong>@nameof(HxSelect<object, object>.SortKeySelector)</strong><br />
		Selects value to sort items. Uses <code>@nameof(HxRadioButtonList<object, object>.TextSelector)</code> property when not set.<br />
		When complex sorting required, sort data manually and don't let sort them by this component. Alternatively create a custom comparable property.
	</li>
	<li>
		<strong>@nameof(HxSelect<object, object>.Data)</strong><br />
		Items to display.
	</li>
	<li>
		<strong>@nameof(HxSelect<object, object>.TextSelector)</strong><br />
		Selects text to display from item. When not set <code>ToString()</code> is used.
	</li>
	<li>
		<strong>@nameof(HxSelect<object, object>.ValueSelector)</strong><br />
		Selects value from item.
	</li>
	<li>
		<strong>@nameof(HxSelect<object, object>.Nullable)</strong><br />
		Indicates whether null is a valid value.
	</li>
	<li>
		<strong>@nameof(HxSelect<object, object>.NullText)</strong><br />
		Text to display for <code>null</code> value.
	</li>
	<li>
		<strong>@nameof(HxSelect<object, object>.NullDataText)</strong><br />
		Text to display when <code>@nameof(HxSelect<object, object>.Data)</code> is <code>null</code>.
	</li>
</ul>

